    <h2>3 enhancements for your organisation...</h2>
<h6><strong>1) Productivity</strong></h6>
<p>From the time it takes to process a request for annual leave or sickness absence, to the time dedicated to monthly reporting within your organisation, absence management takes up a great deal of your HR teams and Line Managers time each month.</p>
<p>e-days aims to cut the time taken to do those jobs down to seconds and minutes, rather than hours and days. With reports easy to create and then scheduled to run monthly, managers only have to take the time to create reports once for them to be produced over and over again as and when they are required.</p>


</div>
    
        <div id="ctl00_ctl00_CorePlaceHolder_DisplayPagePlaceHolder_ctl00_textBlock2_ctl01_ctl00_pnlContentContainer" class="dynamic_callout_container">
	

    <h2>3 enhancements for your organisation</h2>
<h6><strong>2) Accountability</strong></h6>
<p>Although we hope none of our clients become locked in disputes with their employees over long periods of sickness or excessive sickness having to result in dismissal, we know that it can happen.</p>
<p>For occasions like this, e-days ensures employees and employers are accountable with no margin for error as all employee absence data is stored securely on our cloud based system.</p>
<p>When using paper and spreadsheets the margin for error with lost data or documents is high and can lead to legal loopholes being used during employment disputes.</p>


</div>
    
        <div id="ctl00_ctl00_CorePlaceHolder_DisplayPagePlaceHolder_ctl00_textBlock2_ctl02_ctl00_pnlContentContainer" class="dynamic_callout_container">
	

    <h2>3 enhancements for your organisation</h2>
<h6><strong>3) Employee Satisfaction &amp; Wellbeing</strong></h6>
<p>Having an absence management system in place whereby employees are able to access and request holidays at any time can lead to a real increase in employee satisfaction.</p>
<p>As an example, imagine you&rsquo;re looking at some cheap flights online and could really do with putting a request in to your line manager there and then with the hope it will be approved quickly&hellip; with e-days you can do that even if you&rsquo;re at home.</p>


</div>
    
